\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"28796b4dc408292bb5e24f66dfa4d3a34f187b82144505db04f9e694e47af857","event_uuid":"8de3124f-5dad-4547-8188-6d8f2ced33ff","position":{"commit_sha":"9688ddb381e1c106fc158ea1ed4d823b1ff3b315","position":"1784356426945881001-8de3124f-5dad-4547-8188-6d8f2ced33ff"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-212_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"a9f45bda-d9d9-460c-a61d-32796b3f8d2d","comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Code landed: Gerrit change 785 MERGED to origin/main as df0ac80be (LLM-Review +1 + Verified +1, whole-store gate passed). apply_handlers.py promotes swallowed PARTIAL comment drops to outcome[error] behind RECONCILER_FAIL_SILENT_NOOP (create+update; canary augments); new tests isolate the partial-drop gap + add comments/labels canary coverage. ACs 1-4 met. REMAINING: AC5 [operator-attested] — activate REBAR_RECONCILER_FAIL_SILENT_NOOP=1 in reconcile-bridge.yml AFTER the bd80 Jira cleanup lands (else it fails every pass on still-capped tickets). Ticket stays in_progress until then.","timestamp":1784356426945881001}],"created_at":1784340019972554001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"## Why\n\nA reconcile pass with silently-failed sub-ops still reports `OK: applied N of N` / exit 0\n(\"converged\"). Two gaps make sync failures invisible: (1) the silent-no-op canary\n(`apply_handlers.py` ~line 218) only hard-fails behind `RECONCILER_FAIL_SILENT_NOOP`\n(default \"0\" = warn-only); (2) `comment_errors` (swallowed partial comment failures,\n`apply_handlers.py:117-118,195-196`) are recorded NON-fatally and never counted in\n`mutation_failures` (`reconcile.py` ~line 1051), so a partial comment drop yields exit 0.\nConfirmed by the /rebar-debug (b) audit: acli exit-0-on-failure IS detected at the transport\nfloor (`acli_subprocess._check_mutation_failure`), then demoted to non-fatal `comment_errors`.\n\n## What (gate fatality behind the existing flag; keep default OFF)\n\n- `apply_handlers.py`: when `comment_errors` is present AND `_rebar_env(\"RECONCILER_FAIL_SILENT_NOOP\")==\"1\"`,\n  set `outcome[\"error\"]` (so partial comment failures count), mirroring the existing total-no-op\n  canary flag check. Default off ⇒ landing is behavior-neutral.\n- Optional: a per-pass telemetry summary line (silent-no-op count + comment-error count) —\n  always-on, non-fatal (pure visibility).\n\n## Sequencing (CRITICAL)\n\nDo NOT activate fail-loud before the Jira comment cleanup (sibling ticket). The 13 capped\ntickets still have ~7 genuinely-unsynced comments each that bounce off Jira's 5000 cap until\ncleanup; flipping fail-loud first makes the reconciler FAIL every pass on them. Land the\ngated machinery NOW (safe); ACTIVATE (set `REBAR_RECONCILER_FAIL_SILENT_NOOP=1` in\n`.github/workflows/reconcile-bridge.yml` env) only AFTER the cleanup.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] With the flag ON, an outcome carrying `comment_errors` counts toward `mutation_failures`\n      and drives a non-zero pass exit. Proving command: a unit test in\n      `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/apply/` (extend `test_silent_noop_canary.py` / add one) —\n      RED before the change (comment_errors → exit 0).\n- [ ] With the flag OFF (default), behavior is unchanged (comment_errors non-fatal). Regression\n      test asserts this.\n- [ ] The silent-no-op canary already covers TOTAL no-ops for links/comments/labels (verify + a\n      test for comments/labels, not just links — the (b) audit noted links-only coverage).\n- [ ] `make test` green; no new dependency.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] Flag activated in reconcile-bridge.yml AFTER the Jira cleanup lands.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","58b0-104b-777c-4227"]],"parent_id":"58b0-104b-777c-4227","parent_status_uuid":"a0afb4d3-2fa3-4710-98c3-a80379196687","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"48c8-5375-f883-462d","ticket_type":"task","title":"Observability: fail-loud on silent sub-op no-ops + count comment_errors (gated; activate after cleanup)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["7a40d11f-33fb-4629-b681-4f3092707a78","e6e5e9f7-c1a1-464e-9816-ddf8964d5c9d","a0afb4d3-2fa3-4710-98c3-a80379196687","fd1fb1fc-f799-4f10-91e2-a94d72da893c","c341599e-a043-4314-93f3-2711f4086131","8de3124f-5dad-4547-8188-6d8f2ced33ff"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784356426945881002,"uuid":"8b600e95-d1ed-4ba4-ab11-26308bc3a578"}